    <p class="text-gray-700">Our reviews consistently found New Zealand Sauvignon Blancs display intense tropical fruit flavors (passion fruit, grapefruit) with herbaceous bell pepper notes due to higher methoxypyrazine levels. French Sancerre showed more mineral-driven profiles with citrus and wet stone characteristics, reflecting Loire Valley's limestone-rich soils and cooler climate that preserves natural acidity while reducing pyrazine expression.</p>
