    <p class="text-gray-700">Excessive green bell pepper and asparagus flavors typically resulted from high methoxypyrazine levels due to underripe grapes or overcropping in cooler vintages. Our review noted this was most common in cool-climate regions during challenging years, or from producers who harvested too early chasing high acidity at the expense of phenolic ripeness.</p>
